time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
---

Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{2}. Put your parsley in a #bowl{} with the @olive oil{4%tbsp}, half the @ground cumin{1%tsp} and a good squeeze of @lemon{1}(juiced). Add the @British chicken thighs{8}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{pinch} and mix together. Leave your chicken to the side to marinate.

Chop the @red potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) or use a #garlic press{} if you have one. Remove the seeds from the @red chilli{1/2} and finely chop.

Pop your potato on a #baking tray{}. Sprinkle over the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a grind of @black pepper{pinch} and a good drizzle of @oil{}. Toss together to ensure they get a good coating, then put on the top shelf of your oven for ~{30%minutes} until slightly crispy. Give the tray a shake halfway through to ensure they cook evenly!

Now for the bravas sauce. Put a #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} and add your garlic, remaining ground cumin and some chilli (use less chilli if you aren't a fan of heat!). Cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the @tomato passata{2%tbsp}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{pinch}, stir well and cook on low heat for about ~{7%minutes}. Remove from the heat and leave to the side with a #lid{} on.

While your bravas sauce cooks, pop your chicken on a baking tray and put on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Tip: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While your potato and chicken cooks, slice the @courgette{2} into 1cm thick rounds.

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (without any oil) and leave it to get hot for a couple of mins. When the pan is hot, lay in your courgette slices and cook for ~{4-5%minutes} on each side until slightly charred. Season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}, then remove the pan from the heat.

When your potato and chicken are ready, remove them from your oven. Pop your potato onto #plates{} and spoon over some of your bravas sauce. Add your herby cumin chicken, a few of your charred courgettes and enjoy!